The paper deals with collision detection between moving convex polytopes, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The development of new kinetic data structures also falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance of these structures for different types of motion, including translation along a straight line or convex curve, translation along an algebraic trajectory, and algebraic rigid motion (translation and rotation), which are topics in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a certain cover of the motion path by balls, which is a technique used in computational geometry and topology (cs.GR).
